    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-06-13T03:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-06-13T03:35:00-05:00" n="420"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d420">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.51A/1165: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ford</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-06-13T12:00:00+03:25"
                            >June 13, 1944—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received June 13—10:12 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>422. I wish to warn Department that Ebtehaj has turned violently against
                    Millspaugh and open warfare has broken out between the two men. Speaking before
                    Tehran Chamber of Commerce few days ago, Ebtehaj said: “Five days after I reach
                    Washington, Millspaugh will be removed.”<note n="10" xml:id="d420fn10">Abol
                        Hassan Ebtehaj had been appointed Chairman of the Iranian delegation to the
                        United Nations Monetary and Financial Conference to be held at Bretton
                        Woods, New Hampshire, July 1–July 22, 1944; for correspondence regarding
                        this Conference, see <ref target="frus1944v02">vol. <hi rend="smallcaps"
                                >ii</hi>
                        </ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>My letter June 9 to George Allen<note n="11" xml:id="d420fn11">Chief of the
                        Division of Middle Eastern Affairs.</note> gives details of Ebtehaj’s
                    attitude.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Ford</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
